Node.Notes: More likely refers to Hamor than to his son (older translation of this word as prince is misleading).
He was greatly attached/deeply attracted to her.
He tried to win her heart/convince her of his love for her.
A sinful act that is the opposite of wisdom; foolishness in its worst form.
Uncertain. Word originally means to circle, follow an irregular course and later came to mean to trade. Some believe sense here is to travel/roam freely in the land (with original sense).
Bride price that will be paid by the groom to the bride’s family.
Uncertain whether this is a separate item from the bride price or not and if it is a gift to the Dinah's family or to Dinah herself.
Assumes: As for the land, behold, [it is] wide on both hands (i.e., it is large enough) before them.
Only Simeon and Levi carried out the massacre. This apparently refers to the other sons who came in afterwards to take plunder.
Tree shows relative clause modifying city (where they defiled their sister). Could also be because they defiled their sister.
